@node Introduction

1.1 Introduction & Requirements
===============================


Welcome to the MovieDataBase v3.5 Amiga!

 @{"What is the MovieDataBase?" link moviedatabase.guide/1}
 @{"Objective & Distribution  " link moviedatabase.guide/8}

This   package  provides  a  fully  featured,  easy-to-use  graphical  user
interface  (based  on  Stefan Stuntz's @{"MagicUserInterface" link MUI}, so hopefully it
can answer almost any movie query you might have.

Therefore  MUI has to be installed on your system before you try to install
the MovieDataBase.  Kickstart 2.0 or higher is required.

If  you  want to use all features of the MovieDataBase, you need to have at
least   150  MB-diskspace   (more  diskspace  will  be  needed  during  the
@{"installation" link Installation}  process,  depending  on which method you prefer to set up the
database)  and  about 6 MB Ram.  A fast processor and a fast harddisk would
also be very handy, if the time for the installation and data look-up is to
be kept to a minimum.

If  you  have  any  questions  concerning  the  Amiga  Version of the Movie
Database,  please  write to me (André Bernhardt).  General questions on the
Database  should  be  directed  to  the  people  who  are  responsible  for
maintaining  the  Database.  Please refer to the appendix for @{"Addresses" link Addresses}.

@endnode


